from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import style
import numpy as np
A=[]
B=[]
def cal_cost(theta,X,Y):
    m=len(Y)
    predictions=X.dot(theta)
    cost=(np.sum(np.square(predictions-Y)))/(2*m)
    return cost

def gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,learning_rate,iterations):
    m=len(Y)
    cost_history=np.zeros(iterations)
    theta_history=np.zeros((iterations,j))
    for it in range(iterations):
        prediction=np.dot(X,theta)
        theta=theta-(1/m)*learning_rate*(X.T.dot(prediction-Y))
        theta_history[it,:]=theta.T
        cost_history[it]=cal_cost(theta,X,Y)
        if((cost_history[it-1]-cost_history[it])<0.0000001 and it>0):
            print('iterations count:')
            print(it+1)
            break
    return theta,cost_history,theta_history,it

for j in range(2,11):
    print('FOR ORDER:')
    print(j-1)
    print('\n')
    theta=np.random.randn(j,1)
    X=np.zeros((1000,j))
    Y=np.zeros((1000,1))
    x,y=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\train.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
    for itr in range(0,1000):
        for k in range(1,j):
            X[itr][k]=pow(x[itr+1],k)
        Y[itr][0]=y[itr+1]
        X[itr][0]=1
    theta,cost_history,theta_history,it=gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,0.05,5000000)
    print('parameters:')
    print(theta)
    print('Error on Training set:{:0.20f}'.format(cost_history[it]))
    A.append(cost_history[it])
    X1=np.zeros((1000,j))
    Y1=np.zeros((1000,1))
    x1,y1=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\test.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
    for itr in range(0,200):
        for k in range(1,j):
            X1[itr][k]=pow(x1[itr+1],k)
        Y1[itr][0]=y1[itr+1]
        X1[itr][0]=1
    print('Test Error:')
    B.append(cal_cost(theta,X1,Y1))
    print(B[j-2])
    print('\n')

    predictions=X1.dot(theta)
    Z=[]
    for itr in range(0,200):
        Z.append(x1[itr+1])
    a=list(zip(Z,predictions))
    b=sorted(a)
    x_new=[x for x,y in b]
    y_new=[y for x,y in b]
    plt.plot(x_new,y_new)
    plt.title('Predicted values of Labels for Test Data')
    plt.ylabel('Predicted Label')
    plt.xlabel('Feature')

    plt.show()

E_min=[]
F_min=[]
E_max=[]
F_max=[]
def cal_cost(theta,X,Y,l):
    m=len(Y)
    predictions=X.dot(theta)
    cost=(np.sum(np.square(predictions-Y)))/(2*m)
    cost=cost+(l*(np.sum(theta)))/(2*m)
    return cost

def gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,learning_rate,iterations,l):
    m=len(Y)
    cost_history=np.zeros(iterations)
    theta_history=np.zeros((iterations,j))
    for it in range(iterations):
        prediction=np.dot(X,theta)
        theta=theta-(1/m)*learning_rate*(X.T.dot(prediction-Y))
        theta=theta-(learning_rate*l)/(2*m)
        theta_history[it,:]=theta.T
        cost_history[it]=cal_cost(theta,X,Y,l)
        if((cost_history[it-1]-cost_history[it])<0.0000001 and it>0):
            print('iterations count:')
            print(it+1)
            break
    return theta,cost_history,theta_history,it

j=5
l=0.25
print('Lasso regularization for order=4 and l=0.25')
theta=np.random.randn(j,1)
X=np.zeros((1000,j))
Y=np.zeros((1000,1))
x,y=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\train.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
for itr in range(0,1000):
    for k in range(1,j):
        X[itr][k]=pow(x[itr+1],k)
    Y[itr][0]=y[itr+1]
    X[itr][0]=1
theta,cost_history,theta_history,it=gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,0.05,5000000,l)
print('parameters:')
print(theta)
print('Error on Training set:{:0.20f}'.format(cost_history[it]))
E_min.append(cost_history[it])
X1=np.zeros((1000,j))
Y1=np.zeros((1000,1))
x1,y1=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\test.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
for itr in range(0,200):
    for k in range(1,j):
        X1[itr][k]=pow(x1[itr+1],k)
    Y1[itr][0]=y1[itr+1]
    X1[itr][0]=1
print('Test Error:')
F_min.append(cal_cost(theta,X1,Y1,l))
print(F_min[0])
print('\n')
predictions=X1.dot(theta)
Z=[]
for itr in range(0,200):
    Z.append(x1[itr+1])
a=list(zip(Z,predictions))
b=sorted(a)
x_new=[x for x,y in b]
y_new=[y for x,y in b]

E1_m=[]
F1_m=[]
def cal_cost(theta,X,Y,l):
    m=len(Y)
    predictions=X.dot(theta)
    cost=(np.sum(np.square(predictions-Y)))/(2*m)
    cost=cost+(l*(np.sum(np.square(theta))))/(2*m)
    return cost

def gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,learning_rate,iterations,l):
    m=len(Y)
    cost_history=np.zeros(iterations)
    theta_history=np.zeros((iterations,j))
    for it in range(iterations):
        prediction=np.dot(X,theta)
        theta=theta-(1/m)*learning_rate*(X.T.dot(prediction-Y))-(learning_rate*l*theta)/m
        theta_history[it,:]=theta.T
        cost_history[it]=cal_cost(theta,X,Y,l)
        if((cost_history[it-1]-cost_history[it])<0.0000001 and it>0):
            print('iterations count:')
            print(it+1)
            break
    return theta,cost_history,theta_history,it

j=5
l=0.25
print('Ridge regularization for order=4 and l=0.25')
theta=np.random.randn(j,1)
X=np.zeros((1000,j))
Y=np.zeros((1000,1))
x,y=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\train.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
for itr in range(0,1000):
    for k in range(1,j):
        X[itr][k]=pow(x[itr+1],k)
    Y[itr][0]=y[itr+1]
    X[itr][0]=1
theta,cost_history,theta_history,it=gradient_descent(X,Y,j,theta,0.05,5000000,l)
print('parameters:')
print(theta)
print('Error on Training set:{:0.20f}'.format(cost_history[it]))
E1_min.append(cost_history[it])
X1=np.zeros((1000,j))
Y1=np.zeros((1000,1))
x1,y1=np.genfromtxt('C:\\ML\\test.csv',unpack=True,delimiter=',')
for itr in range(0,200):
    for k in range(1,j):
        X1[itr][k]=pow(x1[itr+1],k)
    Y1[itr][0]=y1[itr+1]
    X1[itr][0]=1
print('Test Error:')
F1_min.append(cal_cost(theta,X1,Y1,l))
print(F_min[0])
